 # Orange Pi Zero 3W Engineering Notes

This directory contains engineering notes for using the Orange Pi Zero 3W as a lightweight SwarmDock / SwarmPlug edge node.

## Tested Baseline

| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| Board | Orange Pi Zero 3W |
| OS | Ubuntu Jammy vendor image |
| Kernel | `6.6.98-sun60iw2` |
| Architecture | `aarch64` |
| Role | Lightweight edge node |

## Notes

| File | Description |
|---|---|
| [01-orange-pi-zero-3w-enable-tun-for-tailscale.md](01-orange-pi-zero-3w-enable-tun-for-tailscale.md) | Build and install `tun.ko` so Tailscale can create `tailscale0`. |
| [02-orange-pi-zero-3w-ar9271-ibss-batman-adv-mesh.md](02-orange-pi-zero-3w-ar9271-ibss-batman-adv-mesh.md) | Configure an AR9271 USB Wi-Fi adapter for IBSS/ad-hoc + BATMAN-ADV mesh networking. |

## Network Role

The intended node layout is:

```text
wlan0              management Wi-Fi / LAN / SSH
tailscale0         remote management overlay
USB Wi-Fi          IBSS/ad-hoc mesh underlay
bat0               BATMAN-ADV Layer-2 mesh interface
